CBRE Investors to Launch $1.6 Billion Property Fund, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-09T01:38:56Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-09/cbre-investors-to-launch-1-6-billion-property-fund-ft-reports.html
CBRE Investors will next week launch
the first specialist U.K. property fund for defined contribution
pension investors, the Financial Times reported, citing CBRE
Senior Director Nick Preston. The CB Richard Ellis U.K. Property
Fund, which has been in planning for more than five years, aims
to raise more than 1 billion pounds ($1.64 billion), the FT
said, citing Preston.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
